===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|だれ}}

{{IPAchar|/tare/}} → {{IPAchar|/dare/}}

From earlier ''tare''.<ref name="KDJ">.{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJS">{{R:Daijisen}}</ref><ref name="DJR"/><ref name="SMK5"/>

The ''dare'' form appears from around the {{w|Edo period}}.<ref name="DJR"/> The voicing of the initial {{IPAchar|/t-/}} to {{IPAchar|/d-/}} is likely by analogy with other interrogative demonstratives {{m|ja|何れ|tr=dore||[[which]] [[one]]}}, {{m|ja|何処|tr=doko||[[where]]}}. See etymology 2

Now the primary form, replacing earlier ''tare''.

